6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
8 Article – Natural Resources
9 3–103.
10 (a) (1) There is a body politic and corporate known as the “Maryland
11 Environmental Service”.
12 (2) The Service is an instrumentality of the State and a public corporation
13 by that name, style, and title, and the exercise by the Service of the powers conferred by
14 this subtitle is the performance of an essential governmental function of the State.
15 (b) (1) There are four officers of the Service:
16 (i) An Executive Director;
17 (ii) A Deputy Director;
18 (iii) A Secretary; and
19 (iv) A Treasurer.
20 (2) (i) The four officers of the Service shall be appointed in accordance
21 with this paragraph.
22 (ii) 1. The Executive Director shall be appointed by the
23 Governor, with the advice and consent of the Senate solely with regard to the qualifications
24 for the duties of the office.
25 2. The Executive Director serves at the pleasure of the Board
26 with the concurrence of the Governor and shall receive such compensation as may be
27 determined by the Board.
28 (iii) 1. The Deputy Director shall be appointed by the Executive
29 Director with the approval of the Governor solely with regard to the qualifications for the
30 duties of the office.

