5 Board from among the Board’s members.
6 2. The Secretary and the Treasurer serve at the pleasure of
7 the Board and shall receive such compensation as may be reasonably determined by the
8 Board.
9 (3) The Board of Directors of the Service shall consist of the following
10 members:
11 (i) The Executive Director, who shall serve as a nonvoting member;
12 (ii) THE FOLLOWING TWO MEMBERS, WHO SHALL EACH SERVE
13 AS A NONVOTING MEMBER:
14 1. ONE MEMBER OF THE SENATE OF MARYLAND,
15 APPOINTED BY THE PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE; AND
16 2. ONE MEMBER OF THE HOUSE OF DELEGATES,
17 APPOINTED BY THE SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE;
18 (III) The [State Treasurer] SECRETARY OF PLANNING, or the
19 [State Treasurer’s] SECRETARY’S designee;
20 (iii) (IV) Three members from the public sector in the State in
21 positions responsible for environmental, water, wastewater, or solid waste management;
22 (iv) (V) One member from the private sector in the State with
23 technical, financial, development, or legal experience related to environmental, water,
24 wastewater, or solid waste management;
25 (v) (VI) One member from the private sector in the State with
26 financial experience related to environmental, water, wastewater, or solid waste
27 management; and
28 (vi) (VII) One member from the private sector in the State with
29 experience or expertise in matters related to business ethics, preferably involving board of
30 director ethics and conflicts of interest.
